Set Up Your Development Environment:
Install the necessary tools: Git, CMake, and a suitable text editor (e.g., VSCode).
Clone the Flipper Zero firmware repository from GitHub.
Create a New Plugin Directory:

Navigate to the applications_user directory within the firmware repository.
Create a new directory for your plugin.
Write Your Plugin Code:

Create a new C file for your plugin, e.g., my_plugin.c.
Implement the necessary functions:

#include <furi.h>
#include <gui/gui.h>

void my_plugin_init() {
    // Initialization code here
}

void my_plugin_task() {
    // Main task code here
}

void my_plugin_exit() {
    // Cleanup code here
}

Modify the CMakeLists.txt:

Add your plugin to the CMakeLists.txt file in the applications_user directory:

add_application(my_plugin "my_plugin.c")

Build the Firmware:
Navigate to the root directory of the firmware repository.
Run the build command to compile the firmware with your new plugin:

./fbt

Flash the Firmware:

Connect your Flipper Zero to your computer.
Use the appropriate tool to flash the compiled firmware onto your device:

./fbt flash

Test Your Plugin:
Navigate to the plugins menu on your Flipper Zero.
Run your plugin to ensure it works as expected.
Debug and Iterate:
Use debugging tools to identify and fix any issues.
Iterate on your plugin to add features or improve performance.
